Package com.rb.nonbiz.json

Class JsonApiEnumDescriptor<E extends java.lang.Enum<E> & JsonRoundTripStringConvertibleEnum<E>>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.json.JsonApiEnumDescriptor<E>
public class JsonApiEnumDescriptor<E extends java.lang.Enum<E> & JsonRoundTripStringConvertibleEnum<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
A way to describe an enum for the purpose of documenting an JSON-based API.

We often serialize a Java enum by using strings that are similar in meaning to the Java identifier, but possibly looking different (e.g. JSON API tends to use camelcase instead of capitalized snake case in Java). We have to use this class, because if we ever rename the Java enum class or its enum values, we don't want the API to change, as others may be relying on those specific strings. That is, we can't just write the Java enum's 'Class.getSimpleName()
